headline: Garmin: Q4 Earnings Snapshot
summary: SCHAFFHAUSEN, Switzerland (AP) — Garmin Ltd. (GRMN) on Wednesday reported fourth-quarter earnings of $528.7 million. The Schaffhausen, Switzerland-based company said it had profit of $2.73 per share. Earnings, adjusted for non-recurring costs, were $2.79 per share.

headline: Garmin forecasts upbeat annual results on strong demand for high-end wearables
summary: Garmin forecast annual revenue and profit above Wall Street estimates on Wednesday driven by strong ‌demand for high-end wearables and fitness products. Shares of the ‌navigation-device maker rose more than 15% in early trading and the stock ​was on track for its highest single-day percentage jump since October 2024 if gains hold. The forecasts show Garmin's growth in various markets, including wellness devices, marine systems and private aviation, despite uneven ‌consumer demand.

headline: Garmin (GRMN) Q4 2025 Earnings Call Transcript
summary: Clifton Pemble: Thank you, Teri, and good morning, everyone.  As announced earlier today, Garmin achieved another quarter of outstanding financial results, driven by strong broad-based demand for our products.  Consolidated revenue increased 17% to more than $2,100,000,000, which is a new fourth quarter record, our first quarter to exceed $2,000,000,000.

content.title: Garmin (GRMN) Q4 2025 Earnings Call Transcript
content.summary: Clifton Pemble: Thank you, Teri, and good morning, everyone.  As announced earlier today, Garmin achieved another quarter of outstanding financial results, driven by strong broad-based demand for our products.  Consolidated revenue increased 17% to more than $2,100,000,000, which is a new fourth quarter record, our first quarter to exceed $2,000,000,000.
